		<body xml:lang="en">
			<div>

	<pb n="0001" facs="liv_001285_0001"/><!--pb/@n='1r'-->
<lb/><p rend="right"><placeName>Birkenhead</placeName> 9<hi rend="sup underline">th</hi> March</p>
<lb/><p rend="right"><space extent="2" unit="words"/>1858</p>
<lb/>
<lb/>
<lb/><p rend="no-indent">Dear <persName>Captain Washington</persName></p>
<lb/><p><space extent="2" unit="words"/><persName>D<hi rend="sup underline">r</hi> Kirk</persName> has 
<lb/>applied to me for his 
<lb/>expenses from London 
<lb/>to this place and also 
<lb/>for those incurred during 
<lb/>our detention here<reg>.</reg>

	<pb n="0002" facs="liv_001285_0002"/><!--pb/@n='1v'--> 
<lb/>I don<reg>'</reg>t know what answer 
<lb/>to give him as I did 
<lb/>not know whether they 
<lb/>would be allowed or 
<lb/>not. I told him that 
<lb/>I had seen the different 
<lb/>items of expenditure 
<lb/>and contingencies 
<lb/>of this kind did 
<lb/>not appear among 

	<pb n="0003" facs="liv_001285_0003"/><!--pb/@n='2r'--> 
<lb/>them but I would submit 
<lb/>the matter to you. I did 
<lb/>not think of putting down 
<lb/>my own travelling expenses 
<lb/>as my pay is running 
<lb/>on but if <persName>D<hi rend="sup underline">r</hi> Kirk's</persName>
<lb/>are to be paid all 
<lb/>will of course apply<reg>.</reg>
<lb/>Will you kindly tell 
<lb/>me by a letter per 
<lb/>mail to the <placeName>Cape</placeName> how 
<lb/>I ought to act in this<reg>.</reg>

	<pb n="0004" facs="liv_001285_0004"/><!--pb/@n='2v'--> 
<lb/>I am sorry that the 
<lb/>weather continues so 
<lb/>unpropitious for 
<lb/>us. We are all quite 
<lb/>ready and quite 
<lb/>anxious to start 
<lb/>but the wind forbids<reg>.</reg>
<lb/>I have got the letter 
<lb/>for <persName>Skene</persName> - thanks<reg>.</reg></p>
<lb/><p>I am &amp;</p>
<lb/><p rend="no-indent">David Livingstone</p>
			
</div>
